    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Once your oven is hot, add your <strong>garlic bread</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 8-10 min</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/puttanesca-style-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-meal-deal/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>black olives</strong> in half</p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/puttanesca-style-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-meal-deal/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/puttanesca-style-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-meal-deal/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>tomato & mozzarella tortelloni </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tortelloni</strong> for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> tortelloni</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/puttanesca-style-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-meal-deal/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>capers</strong> and <strong>halved olives</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 1-2 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/puttanesca-style-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-meal-deal/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar </strong>and a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min further or until the sauce starts to thicken</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/puttanesca-style-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-meal-deal/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the <strong>drained tortelloni </strong>to the pan with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>puttanesca-style sauce with tomato & mozzarella tortelloni</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little thick</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/puttanesca-style-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni-meal-deal/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> puttanesca-style sauce with tomato & mozzarella tortelloni </strong>topped with the <strong>remaining chopped parsley</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> garlic bread </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
